@NODE Introduction "Introduction"

@{b}QuickConv@{ub} is a little program which will help you to quickly convert
numbers in Dec, Hex or Bin format and to make simple bit operations. It was born
because I needed it for my programs !. Then my friends (programmers) told me it
was really useful so I decided to distibute it.
    The program is not the usual calculator, as you'll see, because I wanted to
have under my eyes the number expressed in the three bases, all at the same time.
Then I also needed to understand how the bit operators work and so I wrote QuickConv.

    Important: QuickConv works on 32 bit signed numbers (the LONG definition of
C) as I think is the most useful type. It means that (for the Dec base) numbers
will be in the range -2147483648, +2147483647.

QuickConv was written in C with an A1200HD 030/882 OS 3.x.

    Special thanks to:

Jan van den Baard - for GadToolsBox, which I used for the GUI of QuickConv.

Andrea Latina     - for all the help he gives me. He's a great programmer (Ever tried
                    EasyPrint or RainbowSystem ?)

Alessandro Zummo  - for having made distribution possible..

@{b}NOTE:@{ub} I will be glad to @{"receive" LINK Author} Email or postcards from people who
find QuickConv useful.

@ENDNODE


@NODE Requirements "System Requirements"

System Requirements
-------------------

    QuickConv requires at least an Amiga with a 68020 processor and OS 3.X, this due to
the fact that uses new functions not present in previous releases of OS.

@ENDNODE

